  "name": "volume-1-appendix-career-timeline",
  "title": "Appendix: Career Timeline",
  "description": "A structured career timeline spanning Kastner's six-decade arc in computing, from 1960 bookkeeping frustrations through mainframe operation, consulting, vendor marketing, and co-founding Aberdeen Group. The appendix also documents key technology platform transitions witnessed first-hand, Aberdeen Group's complete financial history (1990\u20132006), and a detailed founding chronology of the Transaction Processing Performance Council (TPC).",
